                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, April 12 (PTI): Bombay High Court today allowed a man to continue to live in the flat which is in his wifes name even after their divorce. The couple, in their sixties, got married in 1969. Later, differences arose and the woman shifted to Delhi in 1980.          
	The flat in which they lived in Juhu had been bought in the wifes name. In 1981, during their separation the man filed a suit, claiming ownership of the flat as it had been bought with his money. Later they reached a settlement where she agreed to share the flat with him. In 1997, she filed for divorce, after which the court did not grant the mans plea to be allowed to live in the house. He then appealed in the high court.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Only half of the total bio-medical waste generated in the country is treated while the rest is dumped with municipal solid waste, posing a risk to environment and human health, according to a recent study.                   
	 Kanpur (PTI): A six-year old boy died after he was hit by Samajwadi Party MLA Ashok Kumar Chandels car on Sunday in Hamirpur, police said. The boy was playing outside his home. Chandels wife was in the car. The driver has been arrested.                  
	 Ghaziabad (PTI): Two persons in Uttar Pradesh have been arrested for allegedly raping a Class XI student and making a video clip of the act to blackmail her. The victim used to take private tuition from a teacher in Sahibabad. On September 6, 2009, the teachers husband and his friend offered her tea laced with intoxicants after which she fell unconscious.                  
	 Valsad (PTI): Burglars broke into State Bank of Indias Dungri branch in Gujarat and looted Rs 11.76 lakh on Monday, police said. The guard found the front door broken and the strong room lying open, they added.                  
	 Ahmedabad (PTI): The number of suicides in Gujarat has risen by 10.5 per cent in 2008, over the previous year with housewives constituting the highest number, according to the National Crime Records Bureau.
                                                                                                                                              
